Specify Decimals.

Source: R/specifyDecimals.R
specify_decimal.Rd

Specify the number of decimals to print.

Usage

specify_decimal(x, k)

Arguments

x

Numeric vector.

k

Number of decimals to print.

Value

Character vector of numbers with the specified number of decimal places.

Details

[INSERT].

See also

Other formatting: apa(), pValue(), suppressLeadingZero()

Examples

# Prepare Data
v1 <- rnorm(1000)

# Specify Decimals
specify_decimal(v1, 2)
